PART III: PERSISTENT HOMOLOGY OF SCORE FILTRATION
======================================================================

  Score filtration (n=5):
    Level 0 (Var ≤ 2.0): all 1024 tournaments
    Level 1 (Var ≤ 1.6): exclude transitive, keep 904
    ...

  H-FILTRATION (superlevel sets):
    Threshold h: |{T : H(T) ≥ h}|
    h ≥ 15:   64 tournaments
    h ≥ 13:  184 tournaments
    h ≥ 11:  304 tournaments
    h ≥  9:  544 tournaments
    h ≥  5:  784 tournaments
    h ≥  3:  904 tournaments
    h ≥  1: 1024 tournaments

  CONNECTIVITY OF SUPERLEVEL SETS:
    h ≥ 15: 64 tournaments, 64 connected component(s)
    h ≥ 13: 184 tournaments, 2 connected component(s)
    h ≥ 11: 304 tournaments, 1 connected component(s)
    h ≥ 9: 544 tournaments (too large for exact check)
    h ≥ 5: 784 tournaments (too large for exact check)
    h ≥ 3: 904 tournaments (too large for exact check)
    h ≥ 1: 1024 tournaments (too large for exact check)

  PERSISTENCE DIAGRAM (birth, death) of connected components:
    As threshold decreases, components merge.
    Birth = first h where component appears
    Death = h where it merges with another
    Births at thresholds: []
    Deaths at thresholds: [13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, 11]
